Package: dogtrack
Type: Package
Title: GPS Data Preprocessing Pipeline for Free-Roaming Dog Movement Studies
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Reda", "Zahri",
           email = "reda.zahri@hotmail.com",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0003-4855-757X")),
    person("Inez", "Derkx",
           email = "inez.derkx@swisstph.ch",
           role  = "aut")
  )
Description: A reproducible multi-site GPS preprocessing pipeline for
    free-roaming domestic dog movement data, developed for the Tracking
    Tails project (Towards Rabies Eradication in Africa), University of Bern, Veterinary Public Health Institute. Implements
    four sequential quality filters — HDOP, displacement speed, turning
    angle, and ellipsoidal height — with site-specific thresholds
    automatically derived from static GPS test files. Designed to handle
    data from multiple field sites simultaneously using a single metadata
    workbook and a consistent filename convention.
